The paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing aggregate statistics in networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the sense that it analyzes the convergence rate of the algorithms. The paper discusses the use of local predictors, which is a topic that falls under the category of Signal Processing (cs.SI). The paper also involves network interconnectivity (cs.NI) since the convergence rate is fundamentally limited by network connectivity. Finally, the paper deals with distributed computing (cs.DC) since it involves the computation of aggregate statistics in a distributed manner.
